## 🎭 The HTMX Event System

This is where the magic happens. **No Redux. No state management hell. Just events.**

### Server-side (once, in `Program.cs`):

```csharp
builder.Services.AddSwapHtmx(events =>
{
    // When a todo is created, refresh the list AND show a toast
    events.Chain(
        SwapEvents.Entity.Created("todo"),
        SwapEvents.UI.RefreshList,
        SwapEvents.UI.ShowToast);
        
    // When bulk operation completes, refresh everything
    events.Chain(
        SwapEvents.Entity.BulkUpdated("todo"),
        SwapEvents.UI.RefreshList,
        SwapEvents.UI.RefreshStats,
        SwapEvents.UI.ShowToast);
});
```

### Client-side (in your views):

```html
<!-- This list refreshes automatically when ui.refreshList fires -->
<div id="todo-list"
     hx-get="/Home/TodoList"
     hx-trigger="load, ui.refreshList from:body"
     hx-swap="outerHTML">
</div>

<!-- Stats panel listens too -->
<div hx-get="/Demo/Stats"
     hx-trigger="load, ui.refreshStats from:body">
</div>
```

**That's it.** One action triggers multiple updates across your UI. Zero JavaScript needed.

👉 **See it live:** `/Demo/Index` for a full playground with bulk operations, dynamic panels, and toast notifications.

📚 **Learn more:** [`docs/EVENTS.md`](docs/EVENTS.md)

