## 🧪 Testing That Actually Works

Integration tests for HTMX apps using **Swap.Testing** — assert on partials, headers, DOM content, and HTMX responses.

```csharp
public class TodoFlowTests : IClassFixture<HtmxTestFixture<Program>>
{
    private readonly HtmxTestClient<Program> _client;
    
    public TodoFlowTests(HtmxTestFixture<Program> fixture) 
        => _client = fixture.Client;

    [Fact]
    public async Task Creating_Todo_Updates_List()
    {
        // Act: Create a new todo via HTMX POST
        var response = await _client.HtmxPostAsync("/Home/AddTodo", 
            new { title = "Test HTMX Flow" });
        
        // Assert: Response is successful
        response.AssertSuccess();
        
        // Assert: List now contains our todo
        var list = await _client.HtmxGetAsync("/Home/TodoList");
        await list.AssertContainsAsync("Test HTMX Flow");
        
        // Assert: Server sent the right events
        response.AssertHasSwapEvent("entity.created:todo");
        response.AssertHasSwapEvent("ui.refreshList");
    }
}
```

**Run all tests:**
```bash
dotnet test
```

Tests are **fast**, **reliable**, and **actually test your HTMX behavior** — not just JSON endpoints.

